attributes.alt: You love your pets & feed a good brand of food....at least you thought so. But have you ever taken a look at the label? Many so called “healthy” pet foods have great ads but low-quality ingredients. Not sure what to look for? Look for real food ingredients you can pronounce such as protein, omega 3s & veggies. Avoid grains such as wheat, corn & barley - they can be big allergens that cause digestive problems. Limit starchy carbohydrates, especially legumes, which may be linked to heart disease.
